The paper deals with the problem of writing on a dirty paper in the presence of an adversary, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of an arbitrarily varying channel (AVC) is also a key aspect of the paper, which is another topic in information theory. The presence of an adversary suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also deals with the problem of maximizing the probability of error, which is a topic in statistical inference (cs.SI). The use of additive white Gaussian noise (AWGN) and state suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
